            "privateNotes": "",
            "publicNotes": "<p>Goblins find fire totally fascinating. It makes light. It's great for cooking. It's a fun toy! Some goblins take their people's admiration of fire a little bit too far and into the realm of deadly obsession.</p>\n<p>Goblins who turn their attention to magic so they can learn to make fire from nothing are known as goblin igniters. These flame fanatics can be a great boon to a band of goblin raiders eager to torch their enemies and wreak havoc. More often, however, their presence is a double-edged sword. In the heat of the moment, goblin igniters sometimes lose sight of their goals and simply set fire to anything that will burn—including their own allies!</p>",
            "publication": {
                "license": "ORC",
                "remaster": true,
                "title": "Pathfinder Beginner Box: Secrets of the Unlit Star"
            }
